"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by the Human Rights Watch\n \n&#xa0;\nSummary \nAbout Human Rights Watch\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe exclusion of people with disabilities from services\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBarriers to political participation for people with disabilities\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nViolence and abuse against people with disabilities\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDFID and the rights of people with disabilities \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n15. The UK government should also ensure that its own domestic laws are in compliance with the CRPD and all other human rights laws ratified by the UK relevant to persons with disabilities. This includes, in particular, l\naws governing legal capacity. At the same time the UK could consider sharing its decades of experience of implementing disability discrimination legislation, for example.\n&#xa0;\nDisability and the post-2015 development agenda\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"